 adopted as the patron of Scotland, Russia, and Greece. It has long been among the most popular boys' names in the English-speaking world, especially in Scotland. Its popularity in England was further enhanced by its use as a British royal name for  Prince Andrew  (  b. 1960 ), the Duke of York."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":28,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Andrew Herle was born in 1354, in Isle of Wight, Hampshire, England, his father, Thomas Herle, was 27 and his mother, Maud Thomas, was 22. He married Juliana le Rous about 1365, in England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1392, in Duntisbourne Rouse, Gloucestershire, England, at the age of 38."},"et":{"1354–1392":"1354–1392","1358–1422":"1358–1422","1383–1410":"1383–1410","1328–1358":"1328–1358","1332–1358":"1332–1358","1358":"1358","1422":"1422","1355":"1355","1410":"1410","1354":"1354","1332":"1332","1383":"1383","ca 1365":"umbes 1365","1382":"1382","1392":"1392","1328":"1328","Devonshire, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Duntisbourne Rouse, Gloucestershire, England":"Duntisbourne Rouse, Gloucestershire, England","Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Toddington, Gloucestershire, England":"Toddington, Gloucestershire, England","Crickhowell, Isle Wight, Hampshire, England":"Isle of Wight, Hampshire, England"},"fi":{"1354–1392":"1354–1392","1358–1422":"1358–1422","1383–1410":"1383–1410","1328–1358":"1328–1358","1332–1358":"1332–1358","1358":"1358","1